The Kwara State Command of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC) received 1, 027 cases, bordering on different offences, from the 16 local government areas of the state, in the year 2021. The State Commandant of NSCDC, Makinde Ayinla, stated this during a press conference in Ilorin on Tuesday. Ayinla said that the cases bordered on different offences like theft, assaults, land disputes, rape, criminal breach of trust, burglary and debt among others. He explained that 31 cases were prosecuted with 6 convictions, while 24 cases were still pending in court. “378 are under investigation and 534 were resolved through Alternative Dispute Resolution, ADR. “Three cases were transferred to the appropriate agencies concerned, 50 were withdrawn after due procedure and over N5 million recovered,” he said. The commandant, however, said that six officers from the Command were prosecuted for misconducts, while 45 officers were given award of excellence, at the 2021 End of Year Party and Award Night. Ayinla, said that no death was recorded during the cause of work in the state by operatives of the command.